We can load these properties for both module and data sync as below :

1. Create a new class and use here : final MapConfigProperties mapConfigProperties;
2. As we are using MapConfig and Config from hazelcast lib. it would autowire properties directly from application.yml that are :

hazelcast:
    cache:
        modules-sync:
            cluster-name: modulesSyncCluster or can give somthing more appropriate
            time-to-live-seconds: 60000
            backup-count: 3
            async-backup-count: 3
        data-sync:
            cluster-name: dataSyncCluster or can give somthing more appropriate
            time-to-live-seconds: 60000
            backup-count: 3
            async-backup-count: 3
--------------------------------------------------------------

@Configuration
@NoArgsConstructor(access = AccessLevel.PROTECTED)
public class MapConfigProperties {

    @Bean
    @ConfigurationProperties(prefix = "hazelcast.cache.modules-sync")
    public Config modulesSyncMapConfig() {
        PartitionAware<Config> configPartitionAware = getConfigPartitionAware(loadModulesSyncMapConfig(),
                "moduleSyncEmbeddedDataStore", "moduleSyncEmbeddedDataStoreInstance");
        return configPartitionAware.getPartitionKey();
    }

    @Bean
    @ConfigurationProperties(prefix = "hazelcast.cache.modules-sync")
    public MapConfig loadModulesSyncMapConfig() {
        return new MapConfig();
    }

    @Bean
    @ConfigurationProperties(prefix = "hazelcast.cache.data-sync")
    public Config dataSyncMapConfig() {
        PartitionAware<Config> configPartitionAware = getConfigPartitionAware(loadDataSyncMapConfig(),
                "dataSyncEmbeddedDataStore", "dataSyncEmbeddedDataStoreInstance");
        return configPartitionAware.getPartitionKey();
    }

    @Bean
    @ConfigurationProperties(prefix = "hazelcast.cache.data-sync")
    public MapConfig loadDataSyncMapConfig() {
        return new MapConfig();
    }
    private PartitionAware<Config> getConfigPartitionAware(final MapConfig mapConfig,
                                                           final String mapConfigName,
                                                           final String configInstanceName) {
        return () -> {
            mapConfig.setName(mapConfigName);
            return new Config(configInstanceName).addMapConfig(mapConfig);
        };
    }

}

We can define both dataSyncDataStore and moduleSyncDataStore here as below :

1. moduleSyncDataStore bean can be autowired to get module sync cache.
2. dataSyncDataStore bean can be autowired to get data sync cache.

Later we can define more cache here if needed.

/**
     * Module Sync Watchdog Map.
     *
     * @return Distributed map which contains the cmHandleIds for ModuleSync which are worked upon.
     */
    @Bean
    public Map<String, String> moduleSyncDataStore() {
        final Config mapConfigAttribute = mapConfigProperties.modulesSyncMapConfig();
        final String hazelcastInstanceName = mapConfigAttribute.getInstanceName();
        final MapConfig mapConfig = mapConfigAttribute.getMapConfig("moduleSyncEmbeddedDataStore");
        final Map<String, String> moduleSyncEmbeddedDataStoreMap = getOrCreateHazelcastInstance(hazelcastInstanceName,
                mapConfigAttribute).getMap(mapConfig.getName());
        return moduleSyncEmbeddedDataStoreMap;
    }

    /**
     * Data Sync Watchdog Map.
     *
     * @return Distributed map which contains the cmHandleIds for DataSync which are worked upon.
     */
    @Bean
    public Map<String, String> dataSyncDataStore() {
        final Config mapConfigAttribute = mapConfigProperties.dataSyncMapConfig();
        final String hazelcastInstanceName = mapConfigAttribute.getInstanceName();
        final MapConfig mapConfig = mapConfigAttribute.getMapConfig("dataSyncEmbeddedDataStore");
        final Map<String, String> dataSyncEmbeddedDataStoreMap = getOrCreateHazelcastInstance(hazelcastInstanceName,
                mapConfigAttribute).getMap(mapConfig.getName());
        return dataSyncEmbeddedDataStoreMap;
    }

    public HazelcastInstance getOrCreateHazelcastInstance(final String hazelcastInstanceName, final Config config) {
        HazelcastInstance hazelcastInstance = Hazelcast.getHazelcastInstanceByName(hazelcastInstanceName);
        if (hazelcastInstance == null) {
            return Hazelcast.newHazelcastInstance(config);
        }
        return hazelcastInstance;
    }

